synopsis: Suzuo has just taken a job testing out new power suits.

title.jp: The Colour in Fashion is Purple, Yeah!

synopsis: Everyone hopes that the new power suits will have them get new recruits.
A new family has moved into the building and Suzuo finally meets their daughter in the park.
Strange noises are coming from Sayuri's apartment making people wonder if their complex is haunted.
Suzuo finds out that the villains are getting more money than he is, so he demands more money.
It is so hot everyone decides to go to the pool but they don't have enough to pay the entrance fee. They pool their money together but only one will get in.

The summer kimonos have arrived and everyone is planning to go see the fireworks. Kurisaburou/Marronflower has created a new device to read people's thoughts in the hope that he will learn Dokkoida and Neruloid Girl's true identities.
A TV movie has some of the neighbors suspecting that something is going on between Suzuo and Kosuzu. Kosuzu is confused, too, and worries that Suzuo may have impure feelings for her.
A superstar, Marilyn Ronmoe has gone missing and the GFP has tasked Tampopo and Dokkoida to find her. Of course, she just wanted to take a break and shows up at Suzuo's apartment.

Chief Mogumokkuru is feeling the pressure from his superiors to improve public sentiment for the GFP. The Inspector has decided to create a reality TV show centered on everyone living in the apartments and dispatches a crew and Mogumokkuru to earth.

title.jp: House Cosmos, The Final Day? Yeah!

synopsis: Summer is over and it would seem that trials to determine the best power suit were nothing more than a cover for the development of the Osabaki M5 as the ultimate weapon for the GFP.
Suzuo has his memory back and the alpha-waves of zealousness are on his side as he fights for Tampopo.
